{"TopicId":183815,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"The Van Allen Belts","CreatedByName":"A Random Kerbonaut","CreatedById":196468,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T01:41:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"A Random Kerbonaut","CreatedById":196468,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T01:41:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSurely you all know the Van Allen Belts and the deadly radiation after them. How did Apollo astronauts not get fried from the rays?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-17T01:42:08Z\u0022 title=\u002204/17/2019 01:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by A Random Kerbonaut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Willer Kerman","CreatedById":196246,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T01:49:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe time they spent in the belt was too short to have problems.\u00A0The trajectories were also calculated to circumvent the inner belt.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-17T01:53:28Z\u0022 title=\u002204/17/2019 01:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Willer Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Random Kerbonaut","CreatedById":196468,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T02:01:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI meant OUT of the belt. Where all that radiation is,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlike the Moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-17T02:02:10Z\u0022 title=\u002204/17/2019 02:02  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by A Random Kerbonaut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Willer Kerman","CreatedById":196246,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T02:09:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce again. They have been exposed for a few days, the only effect of which is increased chance of getting cancer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt could have been fatal if they had been caught in a solar storm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-17T02:10:27Z\u0022 title=\u002204/17/2019 02:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Willer Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T02:14:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimply put-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVA belts are primarily atoms, with no electrons from the sun. That, in the VA belt, get caught and focused towards the Earth\u2019s magnetic poles. The VA is donut shaped with the highest amounts towards the outer edges. Average levels of radiation was less than that of an x-ray per day.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow was that handled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApollo had hydrogen rich polymers in the command module. That absorbed rays as they traveled through them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso Apollo spent very little time in the higher radiation areas of the belt and altogether avoided the highest radiation levels of the belts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOutside\u00A0of the belts was relatively low, least compared to the concentrated regions of the VA belts. So the astronauts had a chance to recuperate after the intense hit of radiation to and from the moon\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadiation wise they were safe and had little effect aside from lights seen in astronauts eyes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso astronauts flew to the moon during solar minimum, when solar activity was at its lowest. Further protecting the crew. In the event of a solar storm, there was nothing they could do.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAstronauts had radiation sensors on them and the average per day levels were pretty low.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA channel on YouTube known as Curious Droid does a really good video on this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/lNiscigIgBc?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T02:19:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know the ISS flies through the Van Allen belts pretty regularly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpecifically it flies through the South Atlantic Anomaly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T02:22:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585243\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555467549\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know the ISS flies through the Van Allen belts pretty regularly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpecifically it flies through the South Atlantic Anomaly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich to translate, the SAA, is basically a region where there\u2019s a polar reversal (magnetic north is south and magnetic south is north). This is due to the movement of liquid iron in the Earth\u2019s core moving by a \u201Cjet stream\u201D but of liquid iron. As it moves, so does the poles\u00A0and their strength.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T02:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585238\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555466986\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196246\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Willer Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Willer Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt could have been fatal if they had been caught in a solar storm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the James Michener novel\u00A0\u003Cem\u003ESpace\u003C/em\u003E, ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe fictional Apollo 18 mission to the Far Side of the Moon was hit by a solar storm (sunspot swarm) while a moonwalk was occurring. The pair rushed back to the LEM and performed a hurried liftoff before finally succumbing to the radiation. The pilot in the CM watched the \u003Cem\u003EAltair\u003C/em\u003E lander crash on the surface while being protected by the mass of the SM facing the Sun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a quote that sticks in my mind from that scene. While rushing back to the LEM, in the rover, it is noted that blacks, er, African-Americans, have a lightly higher resistance to radiation due to the pigments in their skin (I don\u0027t know if this is true). One of the pair is black, and the other says (from memory) \u0022Move over brother, so I can sit in your shadow.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-17T12:36:08Z\u0022 title=\u002204/17/2019 12:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ETypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-17T06:32:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555468772\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhave a lightly higher resistance to radiation due to the pigments in their skin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlas, it\u0027s just a little better anti-UV protection.\u003Cbr\u003E\nA spacesuit anyway protects from UV completely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-18T02:17:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585220\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555465315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196468\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Random Kerbonaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/17/2019 at 8:41 AM, A Random Kerbonaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E did Apollo astronauts not get fried from the rays?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m still wondering what do they hear when passing through it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/L1TDePrRomY?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-18T03:22:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585849\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555553844\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m still wondering what do they hear when passing through it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/L1TDePrRomY?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that answers the question. To avoid the radiation astronauts just gotta JUMP!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brotoro","CreatedById":57674,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-18T03:48:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder how many times strangers came up to Dr.\u00A0James Van\u00A0Allen and offered to buy his belt.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-18T22:32:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585220\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555465315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196468\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Random Kerbonaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/16/2019 at 8:41 PM, A Random Kerbonaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow did Apollo astronauts not get fried from the rays?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same way people in Antarctica manage not to freeze.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy using appropriate protective measures.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-19T06:57:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223586296\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555626779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223585220\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555465315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196468\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Random Kerbonaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/17/2019 at 4:41 AM, A Random Kerbonaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow did Apollo astronauts not get fried from the rays?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same way people in Antarctica manage not to freeze.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDrinking?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}